metadata.name: Momentary #244
metadata.description:
Sometimes, life's troubles seem to be immense and endless. They make us run around in despair, helplessly looking in every direction in search of an answer.

It's tough to be in control of those situations until we understand that everything in our life is momentary, the good times are momentary and of course the bad ones.

We tend to forget that life finds its way and that we just need to hold enough to start to see a clear path to follow.

Life is momentary, the good times are momentary and of course the bad ones.

Hold enough.

There is a path to follow.

-------
WARNING
Please, have into consideration that this work requires some CPU power due to the number of points that needs to be drawn on the canvas. Depending on the hardware and work features, the drawing could take some seconds to some minutes to be finished. 
-------

/- Features

/- Color Scheme
-. Vintage graphite
-. Ashes
-. Serenity
-. Blossom
-. Dark chocolate
-. Blue pen

/- Sky Texture
-. Pencil strokes left
-. Pencil strokes right
-. Pointed lines diagonal
-. Pointed lines vertical
-. Crosshatch
-. Clean

/- Celestial Object
-. Fire burst type A
-. Fire burst type B
-. Eclipse
-. Flare
-. Void

/- Terrain QTY.
-. 1 to 5

/- Terrain Type
-. Blasted sand
-. Peaceful sand
-. Rocky ridges

/- Terrain accent
-. True
-. False

/- Dripping ridges
-. True
-. False

/- Frame
-. True
-. False

-------

/- Controls

[p] Save image @ 2000x2300 px.
[Backspace] Pause the animation.
[Enter] Play the animation. 

-------

metadata.name: Forgive Your Sins #23
metadata.description:
This is a colorful remix for #genuary32nd of my late #genuary23 work done on 31st of January!
This is my tribute to Yayoi Kusama (#genuary25) with viscous dots of digital ink thrown in digital liquid and then shaken by digital sine waves (#genuary15) inspired by marbling techniques.

This is the 2nd iteration of my Wasm/Rust fluid simulation engine after "Viscous Circles" collection. Check it on FxHash if you want to know more about the engine behind this generator.

Controls

You can stop at any step if you like the state at this instant, you can restart it, de/increase resolution (default is 4096x4096 to have sharp image, up to 16K x 16K) and snapshot at any resolution.

- H: hide/show help.
- Space - pause/start animation.
- R - restart animation.
- I - hide/show res/fps panel.
- A-Q/D - down/up full resolution
- S - take full resolution snapshot

Now, forgive your sins!

Forgive Your Sins @naibdian 2023 Project made using Opensource WebGL, WASM/Rust/JS libs
#genuary32nd #genuary23 #genuary15 #genuary25

metadata.name: Simple Is Beautiful #12
metadata.description:
As a software engineer the "Simple is Beautiful" principle makes part of my life.
So, while learning creative coding, I decided to focus on simplicity to avoid getting lost in the infinite number of possibilities.

In the art world the "Simple is Beautiful" principle also applies... and I guess it applies to life itself!

This is my first generative project and it was a really wonderful challenge.
Hope you enjoy!

metadata.name: Études(Reissued) #199
metadata.description:
Études(Reissued) is a patched and upgraded version of Études(Project #10993).

Études was originally published on April 16, 2022. Because of technical issues (audio doesn’t play due to external link usage) we prepared this reissue to its current holders.

You can visit the original project with this link - https://www.fxhash.xyz/generative/10993 


This reissue comprises of some fixes and additional new features as mentioned below;

New Features;

- New ‘colored’ mode; now has colored noteheads and stems. Added new sampler for the colored mode: Marimba.
- Added a new synth for ‘inverted & colored’ mode; DuoSynth.

Fixes;

- Fixed canvas size to prevent additional notes being added in live mode. Now it’s consistent.
- Samples are now in the zip rather than in an external link, and won't break in the future.
- More consistent (but still sometimes buggy) sonification and audio playback.
- Fixed some minor issues and re-adjusted some probabilities.


---------------------------------------------------------------------------------

- Click to start the sound -

‘Études’ is a series of generative notation accompanied with sound.

‘Études’ is the first series of the ‘Notations’ collection. ‘Notations’ will explore various notation techniques around the world and will use different sonification techniques and generative music algorithms.

In this series, a sonification process has been used to generate sound.

Some articulations or accidentals intentionally exist due to aesthetic preferences. For example there are some musically meaningless things like vibrato on a piano or a coda sign on a motif. And some notes will play the same pitch (even if they appear apart from one another) depending on the chosen scale.

Sonification tends to work better after 2nd (or even 3rd) play. Some minor audio bugs might occur.

There is a major but a rare bug which we intentionally kept in; it plays a generative piece from indicated pitches rather than just playing the motif only once.

There is a rare possibility that ‘Études’ can generate an ‘electronic’ result which plays with a FM synth instead of piano. 

Probabilities;

- 12 root notes

- 12 different scales

- Dynamics; pp,p,mp,mf,f,ff or none

- Dynamic changes; crescendo and diminuendo or none

- 4 different noteheads

- Several accidentals and articulations

- Vibrato might occur on some outputs

- 3 font styles

- 4 background textures


Made with p5.js
Ilgın İçözü, March 2022(Reissued-September 2022)
@distcollective

metadata.name: Asemic writing #18
metadata.description:
This piece is an expanse on my piece for Genuary 2023 "Asemic".

Amidst the cacophony of our mundane language, a new form of expression arises. Each stroke of ink, each fluid line, each curve and shape, has its own unique voice. Breathing life into the seemingly meaningless, each output is its own language, with its own message for us to interpret and read as we see it. All set on a rich paperlike generated texture.

Asemic writing is a visual form of expression that combines elements of writing and art. It transcends traditional linguistic boundaries, using fluid lines, shapes, and curves to suggest meaning and emotion.

Primary Giving
20% Girls Who Code

Interactions:
T = Toggle background textures
S = Save image
R = Replay writing

metadata.name: Aging and Forgotten #58
metadata.description:
"Aging and Forgotten" is my tribute to the transience of technology and life. In this exhibit, I bring together a collection of discarded technological devices and symbols of aging and death, such as skulls and bones. My goal is to create a powerful commentary on the impermanence of all things and the parallel between the aging of technology and the aging of people. Through the combination of technology and the human, I invite viewers to reflect on their own experiences of aging, loss, and the passage of time. With "Aging and Forgotten," I aim to challenge viewers to consider the impact of our rapidly advancing technology and the ultimate fate of all things, both human and technological.

- look for the gold mode
- press p to export png
- press s to export svg
